            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHumanism%20tells%20us%2C%20%22I'm%20okay%20.%20.%20.%20you're%20okay%22%20and%20says%20that%20salvation%20is%20little%20more%20than%20a%20contribution%20to%20one's%20own%20personal%20happiness.%20As%20Christians%2C%20however%2C%20we%20know%20that%20without%20the%20salvation%20purchased%20by%20Jesus'%20blood%2C%20humanity%20is%20hopeless.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENowhere%20is%20the%20wickedness%20of%20humanity%20described%20in%20more%20graphic%20detail%20than%20in%20Romans%201%20and%20Psalm%2010.%20Paul%20begins%20Romans%20with%20a%20thorough%20description%20of%20the%20wickedness%20of%20humankind%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20justification%20for%20the%20wrath%20of%20God.%20He%20continues%20with%20a%20description%20of%20how%20people%20have%20rejected%20the%20truth%20of%20God%20because%20of%20pride%20(Romans%201%3A21)%20and%20how%20such%20rejection%20has%20caused%20their%20minds%20to%20concoct%20unspeakable%20evils%2C%20such%20as%20idolatry%20and%20sodomy%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%2027).%20In%20Psalm%2010%3A7%2C%20David%20describes%20the%20wickedness%20of%20people's%20motives%20and%20speech%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20abuses%20of%20power%20in%20their%20relationships%20with%20their%20fellow%20man.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBefore%20we%20can%20ever%20get%20people%20saved%2C%20we%20must%20get%20them%20lost.%20Who%20among%20us%20does%20not%20see%20within%20himself%20the%20awful%20fruits%20of%20rebellion%20these%20chapters%20describe%3F%20Let%20us%20thank%20God%20today%20that%20He%20is%20willing%20to%20forgive%20our%20past%20and%20to%20accept%20us%20as%20His%20very%20own%20children.%20We%20should%20be%20so%20grateful%20that%20we%20would%20never%20entertain%20the%20thought%20of%20turning%20our%20backs%20on%20Him.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
